maml:description.maml:para: Gets details about single cache or all caches in given resource group or all caches in given subscription.

The Get-AzureRedisCache cmdlet gets the details about cache or caches depending on input parameters. If ResourceGroupName and Name both parameters are provided than it will return details about specific cache name provided.
If only ResourceGroupName is provided than it will return details about all caches in given resource group.
If no parameters are given than it will return details about all caches in given subscription.
If this parameter is provided along with ResourceGroupName than it will get details about specific cache.
If this parameter is provided with Name than it will give details about specific cache otherwise get details about all cache in this resource group.
If this parameter is provided along with ResourceGroupName than it will get details about specific cache.
If this parameter is provided with Name than it will give details about specific cache otherwise get details about all cache in this resource group.
You can pipe input to this cmdlet by property name, but not by value.
Returns an array of redis caches.

maml:alert.maml:para: The Get-AzureRedisCache cmdlet is included in the Azure Resource Manager module beginning in module version 0.8.9.

command:example.maml:title: Example 1: Get specific redis cache by name
command:example.dev:code:
PS C:\>Get-AzureRedisCache -ResourceGroupName myGroup -Name myexists
ResourceGroupName : myGroup Id : /subscriptions/a559b6fd-3a84-40bb-a450-b0db5ed37dfe/resourceGroups/myGroup/providers/Microsoft.Cache/Redis/myexists Location : North Central US Name : myexists Type : Microsoft.Cache/Redis HostName : myexists.redis.cache.windows.net Port : 6379 ProvisioningState : succeeded SslPort : 6380 MaxMemoryPolicy : VolatileTTL RedisVersion : 2.8 Size : 1GB Sku : Basic

dev:remarks.maml:para: This command gets details about specific redis cache.

maml:description.maml:para: Creates new redis cache.
The New-AzureRedisCache cmdlet creates a new redis cache.
Name of redis cache that we want to create.
Name of resource group under which we want to create redis cache.
Location under which we want to create redis cache.
RedisVersion of redis cache. Default value is 2.8 if not provided.
Size of redis cache. Default value is 1GB or C1. All possible values are C0, C1, C2, C3, C4, C5, C6, 250MB, 1GB, 2.5GB, 6GB, 13GB, 26GB, 53GB.
Sku of redis cache. Default value is Standard. Possible values are Basic and Standard
MaxMemoryPolicy used by redis cache. By default it is null. All possible values are AllKeysLRU, AllKeysRandom, NoEviction, VolatileLRU, VolatileRandom, VolatileTTL
Name of redis cache that we want to create.
Name of resource group under which we want to create redis cache.
Location under which we want to create redis cache.
RedisVersion of redis cache. Default value is 2.8 if not provided.
Size of redis cache. Default value is 1GB or C1. All possible values are C0, C1, C2, C3, C4, C5, C6, 250MB, 1GB, 2.5GB, 6GB, 13GB, 26GB, 53GB.
Sku of redis cache. Default value is Standard. Possible values are Basic and Standard
MaxMemoryPolicy used by redis cache. By default it is null. All possible values are AllKeysLRU, AllKeysRandom, NoEviction, VolatileLRU, VolatileRandom, VolatileTTL
You can pipe input to this cmdlet by property name, but not by value.
Returns details about redis caches with accesskeys.

maml:alert.maml:para: The New-AzureRedisCache cmdlet is included in the Azure Resource Manager module beginning in module version 0.8.9.

maml:description.maml:para: Remove redis cache if exists.
The Remove-AzureRedisCache cmdlet removes redis cache if it exists.
Name of redis cache that we want to remove.
Name of resource group under which cache exists and we want to remove it.
It will remove cache and won't stop to ask for confirmation.
By default this command will remove cache and won't return anything if this parameter is provided than it will return boolean value.
Name of redis cache that we want to remove.
Name of resource group under which cache exists and we want to remove it.
It will remove cache and won't stop to ask for confirmation.
By default this command will remove cache and won't return anything if this parameter is provided than it will return boolean value.
You can pipe input to this cmdlet by property name, but not by value.
Return true is no exception occured.

maml:alert.maml:para: The Remove-AzureRedisCache cmdlet is included in the Azure Resource Manager module beginning in module version 0.8.9.

maml:description.maml:para: Regenerate specific access key of redis cache.

Name of resource group under which cache exists.
Which key we want to regenerate 'Primary' or 'Secondary'.
If this parameter is specified then it won't stop to ask for confirmation.

Name of resource group under which cache exists.
